nd their absence in English relates aspects of the internal structure of -ble to issues pertaining to the eventive properties and syntactico-semantic status of the base nouns. This crosslinguistic proposal implicates central issues in the syntax-semantics-morphology interface, e.g. cross category derivations, locus of variation, or status of impossible words.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2022) 0aEnglish languagexAdjective. 0aEnglish languagexGrammar, ComparativexSpanish. 0aEnglish languagexSuffixes and prefixes. 0aEnglish languagexVerb. 0aGrammar, Comparative and generalxMorphology. 0aMorphologyxElectronic books. 0aMorphology. 0aSpanish languagexGrammar, ComparativexEnglish. 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Linguistics / Semantics.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Backlist Complete English Language 2000-2014 PART1z978311023857008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Backlist Linguistics and Semiotics  2000-2014 (EN)z978311023845708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Linguistics and Semiotics 2000 - 2014z9783110636970oZDB-23-DLS08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDe Gruyter Mouton Backlist 2000-2015z978311074296108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK GESAMTPAKET / COMPLETE PACKAGE 2013z9783110317350oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK PACKAGE ENGLISH LINGUISTICS 2013z978311031724408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK PAKET LINGUISTIK 2013z9783110317237oZDB-23-DSP0 cprintz978161451064240uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978161451065940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781614510659423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781614510659/original  a978-3-11-023845-7  DGBA Backlist Linguistics and Semiotics  2000-2014 (EN)c2000d2014  a97